  <name>SCID</name>
  <summary>A chess database application</summary>
  <developer id="io.github.benini">
     <name>SCID</name>
  </developer>

  <description>
    <p>
      SCID (Shane's Chess Information Database) is a chess database application that allows users to store, organize,
      and search through large collections of chess games. It also includes chess engines for playing against the
      computer and analyzing positions. Any Xboard or UCI compatible engine is supported.
    </p>
    <p>
      SCID displays graphical trends and produces printable reports on players and openings. Using Scid you can also
      play online on FICS, and even study endings with endgame tablebases.
    </p>
    <p>
      Engines included in the package:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Stockfish</li>
      <li>Leela Chess Zero</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

